http://www.thehindu.com/sport/tennis/Zeel-Desai-wins/article13990440.ece

National junior champion Zeel Desai bounced back from a slow start to beat fourth seed Jodie Anna Burrage of Britain 2-6, 6-2, 6-4 in the girls’ final of the ITF grade-3 junior tennis tournament at the CLTA Complex on Saturday.It was the fourth singles title of the season in the international junior circuit for the 16-year-old Zeel, who is trained by coach Todd Clark in Ahmedabad. Zeel had won the grade-4 singles titles in Chennai, Thailand and UAE in the last few months.The 60 ranking points for the current title should help third seed Zeel climb higher from her current career-best junior rank of 151.In the boys’ final, Lingxi Zhao of China outplayed top seed Finn Bass of Britain.The results (finals):Boys: Lingxi Zhao (Chn) bt Finn Bass (GBR) 6-2, 6-2. Girls: Zeel Desai bt Jodie Anna Burrage (GBR) 2-6, 6-2, 6-4.